'''拉爾夫·麥克弗蘭·基納'''（{{lang-en|Ralph McPherran Kiner}}，{{bd|1922年|10月27日|2014年|2月6日|catIdx=Kiner, Ralph}}），前[[美國職棒大聯盟|美國職棒大聯盟]][[外野手|外野手]]，曾經效力於[[匹茲堡海盜|匹茲堡海盜]]、[[芝加哥小熊|芝加哥小熊]]和[[克里夫蘭印地安人|克里夫蘭印地安人]]隊。1946至1952年連續7度蟬聯[[國家聯盟|國家聯盟]][[美國職棒大聯盟全壘打王|全壘打王]]寶座、1949年獲得國家聯盟[[美國職棒大聯盟打點王|打點王]]及6次入選[[美國職棒大聯盟全明星賽|全明星賽]]。1975年，以75.41%的票數入選[[美國國家棒球名人堂|美國國家棒球名人堂]]。

== 名言 ==
*「鳥槍開[[福特汽車|福特]]，重砲手開[[凱迪拉克|凱迪拉克]]。」（{{lang|en|''"Singles hitters drive Fords, and home run hitters drive Cadillacs."''}}）
:根據基納本人表示，這句話實際上是由隊友{{tsl|en|Fritz Ostermueller|弗里茨·奧斯特穆勒}}所創造<ref>Johnson, Vince. [http://www.mediafire.com/view/874f1i1aijix138/.png "Once Over Lightly"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mediafire.com/view/874f1i1aijix138/.png |date=20210817220321 }}. ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''. January 7, 1949. Retrieved December 2, 2018. "Once, while Kiner was trying futilely to place his hits, old Fritz Ostermueller came through with a sage observation. 'Ralph,' he said, 'the right-hand batters who hit to right field are driving Fords. The right-hand batters who hit over the fence in left are driving Cadillacs.' Kiner, by the way, is driving a Cadillac."</ref><ref>Kiner, Ralph; Peary, Danny. [https://www.nytimes.com/2004/04/04/sports/backtalk-the-view-from-kiner-s-korner.html "BackTalk; The View From Kiner's Korner"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/04/04/sports/backtalk-the-view-from-kiner-s-korner.html |date=20210929181908 }}. The New York Times. April 4, 2004. Retrieved December 2, 2018. "Another quote that has been attributed to me is, 'Home-run hitters drive Cadillacs and singles hitters drive Fords.' That was actually first said by my Pirates teammate, pitcher Fritz Ostermueller."</ref>。

